@page "/div-section-main"
<PageTitle>Div / Section / Main - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="div-section-main">Div / Section / Main</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Semantic HTML wrapper components that render div, section, and main elements
                with design-system-aware class names.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <h3>Div</h3>
            <pre><code>&lt;Div Class="container"&gt;
    Generic container content.
&lt;/Div&gt;</code></pre>

            <h3>Section</h3>
            <pre><code>&lt;Section&gt;
    A thematic grouping of content.
&lt;/Section&gt;</code></pre>

            <h3>Main</h3>
            <pre><code>&lt;Main&gt;
    Primary page content.
&lt;/Main&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="common-parameters">Common Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Id</td><td>string?</td><td>HTML id attribute.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Style</td><td>string?</td><td>Inline styles.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>AriaLabel</td><td>string?</td><td>Accessibility label.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="div-section-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Div / Section / Main</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Div / Section / Main</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, Div, Section, and Main components render as their standard HTML
                elements. Bootstrap does not have a specific component class for these semantic
                containers — they serve as layout building blocks to which you apply Bootstrap
                spacing, display, and grid utilities. Pass Bootstrap utilities through the
                Class parameter to control the container behavior within the Bootstrap grid.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="div-section-daisyui">DaisyUI Div / Section / Main</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Div / Section / Main</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, Div, Section, and Main components render as standard HTML elements
                and accept any Tailwind utility classes through the Class parameter. DaisyUI
                provides no opinionated class names for these generic containers — they are
                building blocks that you style with Tailwind utilities. Use them as structural
                wrappers around DaisyUI-styled components like Card and Navbar.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="div-section-basecoat">Basecoat Div / Section / Main</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Div / Section / Main</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, Div, Section, and Main components behave identically to the DaisyUI
                context — they render as plain HTML elements styled with Tailwind utilities passed
                via the Class parameter. Basecoat applies no default classes to these generic
                containers. They are the primary structural wrappers for composing Basecoat-styled
                component trees.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("div-section-main", "Div / Section / Main"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("common-parameters", "Common Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("div-section-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5", 2, "bootstrap"),
    new TocItem("div-section-daisyui", "DaisyUI", 2, "daisyui"),
    new TocItem("div-section-basecoat", "Basecoat", 2, "basecoat")
])" />

</div>
